  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Preeclampsia is a systemic pregnancy disorder and is associated with an increased
      cardiovascular risk later in life. This study will characterize myocardial tissue in patients
      after preeclampsia compared to controls and investigate potential functional and structural
      changes in the heart of preeclamptic women primarily with two methods: cardiovascular
      magnetic resonance imaging and echocardiography. A comparison between these two methods,
      where appropriate, is also envisaged.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
